00:46:38.495 --> 00:46:39.661
Who knows anymore?

766
00:46:43.518 --> 00:46:46.552
<i>Can I have
your attention. please?</i>

767
00:46:46.621 --> 00:46:48.581
<i>Hey. it's Hannah.</i>

768
00:46:49.690 --> 00:46:50.906
<i>Hannah Baker.</i>

769
00:46:52.326 --> 00:46:53.959
<i>That's right.</i>

770
00:46:54.028 --> 00:46:57.062
<i>Don't adjust your</i>
<i>whatever device you're</i>
<i>hearing this on.</i>

771
00:46:58.065 --> 00:46:59.665
<i>It's me.</i>

772
00:46:59.734 --> 00:47:01.467
<i>Live and in stereo.</i>

773
00:47:02.987 --> 00:47:04.503
<i>No return engagements.</i>

774
00:47:04.572 --> 00:47:06.439
<i>no encore...</i>

775
00:47:06.507 --> 00:47:09.553
<i>a huge</i>
<i>congrats to our Tiger team</i>
<i>for Saturday's win.</i>

776
00:47:09.577 --> 00:47:11.777
<i>A special shout-out
to Zach Dempsey.</i>

777
00:47:11.846 --> 00:47:14.447
<i>who crushed it with 28 points.</i>

778
00:47:14.515 --> 00:47:15.998
<i>In other athletic news.</i>

779
00:47:16.067 --> 00:47:17.950
<i>the Lady Tigers won their game</i>

780
00:47:18.018 --> 00:47:20.085
<i>by a score of 54-32.</i>

781
00:47:23.341 --> 00:47:25.752
Thought you said
this wasn't a test.

782
00:47:25.776 --> 00:47:27.504
'Cause this looks like a test.

783
00:47:27.528 --> 00:47:29.595
It's not. Mr. Pratters.
I assure you.

784
00:47:29.664 --> 00:47:32.698
It is a character-building
questionnaire that assesses

785
00:47:32.767 --> 00:47:34.700
personal strengths
and weaknesses.

786
00:47:54.272 --> 00:47:55.738
Excuse me. Mrs. Bradley?

787
00:47:55.807 --> 00:47:57.490
Yes. Clay.

788
00:47:57.558 --> 00:47:59.775
How important was it to you
to help Hannah Baker?

789
00:48:02.447 --> 00:48:05.247
Extremely important to me.
Clay. Why do you ask?

790
00:48:07.918 --> 00:48:10.235
Remember that note you got
in your bag last year?

791
00:48:11.839 --> 00:48:14.079
The one about not
feeling anything anymore?

792
00:48:18.278 --> 00:48:19.445
It was from Hannah.

793
00:48:21.615 --> 00:48:24.032
Okay. uh. why do you
think that is?

794
00:48:26.437 --> 00:48:27.581
Mrs. Bradley?
Yes?

795
00:48:27.605 --> 00:48:30.172
Sorry to interrupt.
but I need Mr. Jensen.

796
00:48:30.241 --> 00:48:31.523
Okay. Mr. Porter.

797
00:48:31.592 --> 00:48:34.159
Clay. we can continue this
discussion at another time.

798
00:48:36.147 --> 00:48:37.946
I have to say.
I'm a little surprised.

799
00:48:38.849 --> 00:48:40.182
What? Why?

800
00:48:40.251 --> 00:48:41.684
I know it's been a few weeks.

801
00:48:41.753 --> 00:48:44.273
but you seem like
the type of kid to follow
through on a promise.

802
00:48:45.356 --> 00:48:46.772
Don't worry. Clay.

803
00:48:46.841 --> 00:48:48.306
I almost forgot too.

804
00:48:49.410 --> 00:48:50.976
Forgot what?

805
00:48:51.044 --> 00:48:53.490
Courtney and Clay.
these are our new
foreign exchange students

806
00:48:53.514 --> 00:48:55.380
joining us this semester.

807
00:48:55.449 --> 00:48:59.852
This is Jhene. Fynn.
Mahla and Deep.

808
00:48:59.921 --> 00:49:02.571
Uh. Courtney and Clay
will be helping you out.

809
00:49:02.640 --> 00:49:05.707
They are on the
Honor Board and they'll be
giving you the tour.

810
00:49:05.776 --> 00:49:07.142
The insider's tour!

811
00:49:07.211 --> 00:49:09.744
All the secrets that
you need to know.

812
00:49:12.917 --> 00:49:13.999
Okay. great.

813
00:49:17.488 --> 00:49:18.821
<i>So as you can see.</i>

814
00:49:18.889 --> 00:49:22.091
it's one of the finest
high school parking lots
in the world.

815
00:49:22.159 --> 00:49:23.592
Oh. and right here
is the library.

816
00:49:23.661 --> 00:49:27.412
where you can find books
and tables and chairs
and all that stuff.

817
00:49:27.481 --> 00:49:28.748
state-of-the-art computers.

818
00:49:28.816 --> 00:49:31.083
at least if the art
was ten years ago.

819
00:49:31.152 --> 00:49:32.401
and friendly librarians.

820
00:49:32.470 --> 00:49:35.304
Not super bright always.
but friendly.

821
00:49:38.809 --> 00:49:40.509
Oh. wait. everyone.

822
00:49:40.578 --> 00:49:43.262
It's Justin Foley
and Zach Dempsey.

823
00:49:43.330 --> 00:49:45.548
star basketball players
here at Liberty High.

824
00:49:45.616 --> 00:49:47.717
Hey. Justin. where's my bike?

825
00:49:48.386 --> 00:49:49.785
Justin stole my bike.

826
00:49:49.854 --> 00:49:51.347
What the fuck?
What are you doing?

827
00:49:51.371 --> 00:49:53.450
I'm giving our new foreign
exchange students a tour.

828
00:49:53.474 --> 00:49:55.886
Figured they should know
who owns the school.
right. you guys?

829
00:49:55.910 --> 00:49:56.993
Clay.

830
00:49:57.061 --> 00:49:58.427
Right. right. Moving on.

831
00:49:58.496 --> 00:49:59.496
Where were we?

832
00:49:59.563 --> 00:50:00.596
Right. The auditorium.

833
00:50:00.664 --> 00:50:02.965
Oh. oh. but before we go...

834
00:50:03.034 --> 00:50:05.434
I want to show you
something super cool.

835
00:50:05.503 --> 00:50:07.370
Okay?
Clay. cut it out.

836
00:50:08.072 --> 00:50:10.139
Look at these lockers.

837
00:50:10.208 --> 00:50:11.740
They all look alike. right?

838
00:50:13.777 --> 00:50:14.777
Not this one.

839
00:50:17.081 --> 00:50:19.181
This one is special.

840
00:50:19.249 --> 00:50:21.211
It belonged to a girl
who killed herself.

841
00:50:21.235 --> 00:50:22.851
Clay. come on.

842
00:50:22.920 --> 00:50:25.598
You see all these
"don't kill yourself"
posters up on the wall?

843
00:50:25.622 --> 00:50:27.022
They weren't up before.

844
00:50:27.091 --> 00:50:29.358
They put them up
because she killed herself.

845
00:50:29.427 --> 00:50:30.559
And why did she do it?

846
00:50:30.627 --> 00:50:32.472
Because the kids here
treated her like shit!

847
00:50:32.496 --> 00:50:33.862
Jensen. that's enough.

848
00:50:33.931 --> 00:50:35.875
But no one wants to admit it.
so they paint over
the bathrooms

849
00:50:35.899 --> 00:50:38.678
and put up a memorial.
because that's the kind
of school that this is.

850
00:50:38.702 --> 00:50:41.614
Everyone is just so nice
until they drive you
to kill yourself.

851
00:50:41.638 --> 00:50:43.718
And sooner or later.
the truth will come out.

852
00:50:45.742 --> 00:50:46.841
It's gonna come out.

853
00:50:51.265 --> 00:50:54.066
Right. Tony? Right?
You know the truth.

854
00:50:54.135 --> 00:50:55.135
Clay.

855
00:50:56.871 --> 00:50:59.231
I think you should
come with me right now.

856
00:51:00.208 --> 00:51:01.990
Get to class. everybody!

857
00:51:02.743 --> 00:51:04.309
All you. get to class.

858
00:51:07.514 --> 00:51:08.714
Welcome to Liberty High.

859
00:51:09.650 --> 00:51:10.890
Let's go.

860
00:51:20.478 --> 00:51:21.478
Okay.

